Popular actress Kemi Afolabi has shown her appreciation to her colleagues for helping her during her down time recently. The actress took to her Instagram page to thank her colleagues and friends for helping her when she announced the robbery attack and the illness that almost took her life. Dayo Kujore’s family announces burial arrangements of Juju Singer Djokovic declared public threat, detained again in Australia Sharing a collage video of those that featured the likes of Metcy Aigbe, Odunlade Adekola, she wrote, “Wowed by y’all doing EXTRA. You did not only come all the way to my home, cash, provisions and gift was excess. A heartfelt thank you for the well wishes from family, friends, colleagues, fans, Kemi Afolabi family, Nigerians home and abroad after the armed robbery attack, May it not be your portion. “The love has been massive since I shared the change in my health status. Everyone tried to reach out to me by every means possible, worried, concerned, celebrated me, calls, messages of prayers and shared even their own health journey to motivate me.”(sic) In December 2021, the actress disclosed that she suffered from an undisclosed illness that nearly took her life, also, in January 2022 she was also attacked by robbers on her way back from a movie set,